14/12/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The European Commission (EC) on Wednesday (December 13th) approved a mechanism to monitor the level of reforms Bulgaria and Romania are making in terms of the judiciary and combating corruption and crime, sources of concern in the latest EC progress reports on the two countries. The mechanism, which would be applied after the countries' accession in January, would require the filing of regular reports, for review by the EC. (Sega, Adevarul - 14/12/06)
